Have received a new request to include the ability to link to Confluence pages from within custom field in Jira. 

JRACLOUD-32835
{noformat}
It would be highly advantageous to be able to link directly to a Confluence page from within the issue creation dialog using a custom field.We already have the 'linked issues' field available that mirrors the more actions -> link -> jira issue page. I'd like to see the same functionality extended to more actions -> link -> confluence page. {noformat}

{panel:title=Update 28th July 2021}
Thank you for your patience - this issue has been resolved for users in the New Issue View experience.  If you are still experiencing any issues please let us know on this ticket.
{panel}
h3. Issue Summary

Attachment section is failing to load
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a ticket and upload some attachments
 # Now try to access this same ticket
{noformat}
https://${site_name}.atlassian.net/browse/${issue_key}
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results

Section panel with attachments should load just fine for all the users.
h3. Actual Results

The attachment section fails to load for specific users.
 !failure.png|thumbnail!

ps. This is an issue that affects only specific users. For example, the user "John Doe" can't see the attachments for "ABC-123" but "Jane Doe" can.
h3. Workaround

Currently, there is no workaround for this bug.

{color:#FF0000}-Using the old issue view seems to resolve the problem for the affected users.- (Deprecated) {color}
{noformat}
https://${site_name}.atlassian.net/browse/${issue_key}?oldIssueView=true
{noformat}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-31190].
  {panel}

Currently, for commenting using mail handlers (Add a comment from none quoted email body, Add a comment from the entire email body and Add a comment before a specified marker or separator in the email body) does not posess the option to select which project to add the comment on. The mail handler will comment on respective issues provided there is a issue key available on the subject field without the ability to limit the commenting only to a particular project.

Example: I have project A (PRA), B(PRB) and C(PRC) created, and I configured my mail handler to "Add a comment before a specified marker or separator in the email body". My users can actually comment on all the projects. What if I do not want the issues in PRB and PRC to be commented, there is no way of doing so.

Therefore, I would suggest that commenting from mail handler can also associated with projects so that administrators have the selection of which project that the mail handler will handle the commenting (something similar to the create issue selection on the mail handler).

Right now only component names can be accessed with Jira Automations. A sample Use Case would be to create sub-tasks for every component added to an issue and assigning their component lead to those.

Accessing to the component lead could be possible like this:
{code:java}
{{issue.fields.component.lead.displayName}{code}
Right now this is not possible without an API call which is taking way longer and is much more complicated and much more prone to error.
